)</i> ‘entire’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, but its popularity in medieval England was greatly enhanced by the fact that it had been borne by the mother of Edward the Confessor, herself a Norman. In modern times, it was only in moderate use early in the 20th century but rose sharply in favour in the 1970s and has since remained perennially popular."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Emma Basset de Centreville was born about 1007, in Ouilly-le-Vicomte, Calvados, Lower Normandy, France as the daughter of Osmond Bassett de Centreville and unknown wife of Osmund de Centville. She married Hugh de Vernon Count of Meulan in 1028. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1030, in Vernon, Eure, Normandy, France, at the age of 24."},"et":{"about 1007–1030":"umbes 1007–1030","0995–Female":"0995–Surnud","1007–1030":"1007–1030","1009–1100":"1009–1100","–1082":"–1082","1000–1053":"1000–1053","1030–1070":"1030–1070","1030–1089":"1030–1089","0960–1007":"0960–1007","–Female":"Surnud","1000":"1000","1053":"1053","1030":"1030","1082":"1082","1070":"1070","1007":"1007","1028":"1028","0995":"0995","about 1007":"umbes 1007","0960":"0960","1089":"1089","1100":"1100","before 1030":"enne 1030","1009":"1009","Vernon, Eure, Normandy, France":"Vernon, Eure, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Ouilly, Calvados, Lower Normandy, France":"Ouilly-le-Tesson, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Vernon Castle, Eure, Haute-Normandie, France":"Vernon, Eure, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Europe":"Europe","Ouilly le Vicomte, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France":"Ouilly-le-Vicomte, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1007–1030":"noin 1007–1030","0995–Female":"0995–Kuollut","1007–1030":"1007–1030","1009–1100":"1009–1100","–1082":"–1082","1000–1053":"1000–1053","1030–1070":"1030–1070","1030–1089":"1030–1089","0960–1007":"0960–1007","–Female":"Kuollut","1000":"1000","1053":"1053","1030":"1030","1082":"1082","1070":"1070","1007":"1007","1028":"1028","0995":"